      "content": "Okay, that \"routine system optimization\" angle is much better. If we go with that, we basically imply the exposure was a side effect of us actually making things safer. \n\nNow, if a tech journalist asks specifically, \"Wait, if this was a scheduled optimization, why did the emails appear in a public bucket?\" how do we answer that? Can we say it was a temporary sync discrepancy during the transition to the new security protocol? I want a response that satisfies their curiosity without admitting we just forgot to lock the bucket.",
